Reasoning: The paper deals with the computational power of positive Turing reductions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. Specifically, it compares the power of positive Turing reductions to NP and DP, which are classes in the boolean hierarchy. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) in its analysis, which are less central but still relevant topics.
